                    <li><b>Delay Coverage:</b> In most travel insurance policies, a delay beyond a certain specified number of hours becomes eligible for reimbursement of accommodation and meals, as well as some transportation costs.</li>
                    <li><b>Cancellation Coverage:</b> This coverage allows passengers to file claims if they cancel a trip because of unexpected incidences, like getting sick or some weather-related happenings, which lead to flight cancellations.</li>
                    <li><b>Additional Expenses:</b> Keep the receipts for all the other expense types, including food, hotels, and transport. Submit them all to your insurer for a refund.</li>
                </ul>
