                <h2>5. Foreseeing Delays in Advance</h2>
                <p>When you know a long flight is going to be delayed for a considerable period, the best way to tackle the situation is to be prepared. Put things in your carry-on that make for comfort, convenience, and staying connected:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><b>Chargers and Gadgets:</b> Have your cell phone updated to include chargers for its accompanying devices, staying in touch for reasons of rebooking and updating flight status.</li>
